    reflection:'Elihu, the youngest voice in the Book of Job, dared to challenge the older men\'s confident but flawed counsel. It\'s an uncomfortable but important truth: age does not automatically guarantee correct judgment. Job\'s friends were experienced, respected, and utterly wrong in how they diagnosed Job\'s suffering. Humility requires elders to remain open to correction, even from someone younger, rather than assuming decades of life have made them immune to error. Wisdom is not measured in years alone but in a heart that stays teachable regardless of how many years have passed.',
