    ref:'Proverbs 17:27',
    imgQuery:'Dahilayan forest zipline Bukidnon Philippines',
    reflection:'Understanding does not require lengthy explanation; often, the wisest people say the least, having learned that not every observation needs to be voiced and not every argument needs to be won. As decades of experience give you more and more to say on nearly any subject, this proverb offers a gentle check: restraint itself is a form of excellence. In family gatherings, church meetings, and quiet conversations with grandchildren, practice choosing fewer, more deliberate words rather than filling every silence with everything you know.',
