    verse:'Now also when I am old and greyheaded, O God, forsake me not; until I have shewed thy strength unto this generation.',
    ref:'Psalm 71:18',
    imgQuery:'Cagbalete Island sandbar Quezon Philippines',
    reflection:'The psalmist\'s prayer is remarkably purposeful for someone aging: not simply asking God for comfort in old age, but asking for enough strength and time to finish telling the next generation about God\'s power. This reframes the later years not as a quiet retreat from purpose but as an urgent, precious window for testimony. What has God\'s strength looked like in your life — through illness, financial hardship, years of separation from family, unexpected provision? These stories, told plainly to a younger generation, may be some of the most important work left for you to do.',
