    verse:'Jesus wept.',
    ref:'John 11:35',
    imgQuery:'Vigan cobblestone Calle Crisologo Ilocos Sur Philippines',
    reflection:'Two words, and yet they carry an entire theology of grief. Jesus, who knew He was about to raise Lazarus from the dead moments later, still wept at the tomb. He did not skip mourning because He knew the ending would be good. This matters for those of us tempted, in our older, more faith-seasoned years, to rush past grief with pious phrases — \'God\'s plan,\' \'better place\' — before we have actually let ourselves feel the loss. If the Son of God wept at a grave He was about to empty, then weeping at your own losses, even with hope intact, is not a lack of faith. It is following His example exactly.',
