    imgQuery:'Siargao Cloud 9 waves Surigao del Norte Philippines',
    reflection:'Retirement after decades of overseas work is often described as freedom, but for many it feels like a valley — the loss of identity, routine, purpose, and the coworkers who became a second family. Add to that the loss of a spouse or sibling in these same years, and the valley grows darker still. David does not promise the valley will be short or well-lit. He promises presence — \'you are with me\' — which changes everything about how the walking feels, even when the darkness itself does not lift. Your worth was never in your job title or your remittance slip; it rests in being walked alongside by the Shepherd who never clocks out.',
