    verse:'For I am convinced that neither death nor life... will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.',
    ref:'Romans 8:38-39',
    imgQuery:'Mount Pulag sea of clouds Benguet Philippines',
    reflection:'This verse is usually read as a promise about our relationship with God, and it is — but it also quietly answers a fear many grieving people carry: did death separate my loved one from God\'s love, from His care, from His presence? Paul\'s answer is an emphatic no. Not death, not any power, nothing can sever a believer from that love, not even at the moment of dying alone, far from family, in a hospital bed overseas. If your loved one trusted Christ, their final moment, however lonely it looked from the outside, was still held entirely inside a love that nothing — not distance, not death itself — could interrupt.',
    wisdom:['Death cannot cut a believer off from God\'s love','A lonely-looking death is not a love-less death','This promise covers both the living and the departed'],
