    verse:'Your eyes saw my unformed body; all the days ordained for me were written in your book before one of them came to be.',
    ref:'Psalm 139:16',
    imgQuery:'Verde Island Passage Batangas coastline Philippines',
    reflection:'For those grieving a life that ended earlier than expected — a spouse gone too soon, a child lost decades ago that is still quietly carried, a friend who did not get the long retirement they had planned — this psalm offers a difficult but steadying truth. Every day of that life, however short it felt to those left behind, was already written and known by God before it began. This does not make the loss painless, but it does mean the life was never a mistake, an accident, or unfinished business from God\'s perspective. It was complete in His sight, fully seen and fully known, even the days you wish had been more.',
    wisdom:['A life that felt too short was still complete in God\'s sight','God\'s knowledge of our days precedes our birth, not just our death','A shortened life is not an unfinished one to God'],
    questions:['Is there a loved one whose life felt \'too short\' to you — could you thank God this week for the days they did have, fully known by Him?'],
