    verse:'Teach us to number our days, that we may gain a heart of wisdom.',
    ref:'Psalm 90:12',
    imgQuery:'Guimaras mango orchard sunset Philippines',
    reflection:'Loss has a strange way of making the remaining days feel both more precious and more fragile at once. After burying a spouse, a sibling, or close friends, it is common to become sharply aware of your own mortality in a way you weren\'t during the busy working years. Moses, who wrote this psalm after watching an entire generation die in the wilderness, was no stranger to loss on a massive scale. His prayer is not for more days, but for wisdom to number the ones remaining — to spend them well rather than simply survive them. Grief, painful as it is, can become the very teacher that gives this numbering its urgency and its meaning.',
