    ref:'1 Peter 5:7',
    imgQuery:'Sirao flower garden hills Cebu Philippines',
    reflection:'Widowhood or widowerhood in the later years brings a unique flood of anxieties — about finances now managed alone, about health decisions with no one to consult, about simply getting through ordinary days that used to be shared. Peter\'s instruction is not a dismissal of these very real worries, but a direction for where to place them. \'Casting\' implies an active, deliberate motion — not just hoping the anxiety fades on its own, but consciously handing it over, again and again, because it will likely return and need handing over again. He cares for you personally, Peter insists, not generically — a promise particularly needed by someone who has just lost the person who cared for them most closely on earth.',
