    verse:'For to me, to live is Christ and to die is gain.',
    ref:'Philippians 1:21',
    imgQuery:'Legazpi Mayon volcano backdrop Albay Philippines',
    reflection:'Paul wrote this from prison, torn between wanting to stay and serve the church, and wanting to depart and be with Christ — both, he says, are genuinely good options, which is a striking claim from someone facing possible execution. For those grieving a loved one who has passed, this verse can reframe death not merely as tragedy but, for the one who has gone, as gain — arrival, not just departure. This does not erase your loss; the gain is theirs, the grief is yours, and both are real simultaneously. But it may ease the sting slightly to remember that wherever your loved one is now, according to this promise, they have not lost — they have gained immeasurably.',
