    verse:'So with you: Now is your time of grief, but I will see you again and you will rejoice, and no one will take away your joy.',
    ref:'John 16:22',
    imgQuery:'Bukidnon highlands sunrise Mindanao Philippines',
    reflection:'Jesus spoke these words to disciples about to lose Him to the cross, promising that their current grief was real but temporary, and that a coming joy would be so secure that nothing — not even future loss — could take it away again. This is a rare kind of promise: not just joy, but unassailable joy. For someone who has lost a spouse after decades of marriage, a promise of ordinary happiness might feel hollow, easily undone by the next loss life brings. But this joy is different — rooted in reunion with Christ Himself, and eventually with those we love in Him, secure against every future grief that might otherwise threaten to take it away again.',
