    verse:'I have fought the good fight, I have finished the race, I have kept the faith.',
    ref:'2 Timothy 4:7',
    imgQuery:'Puerto Galera coral coast Oriental Mindoro Philippines',
    reflection:'Paul wrote these words near the end of his life, facing execution, looking back rather than forward. There is something deeply fitting about applying this verse to a loved one you have lost — especially one who, like so many OFWs, fought hard through decades of sacrifice, distance, and labor to provide for their family, and kept their faith through all of it. Their race is finished now, and it was a good fight, however imperfect, however unfinished it may feel to you watching from this side. Let this verse become a eulogy you can genuinely say over them, not empty praise but an honest accounting of a race well run.',
