    verse:'In peace I will lie down and sleep, for you alone, LORD, make me dwell in safety.',
    ref:'Psalm 4:8',
    imgQuery:'Camarines Norte Calaguas Island Philippines',
    reflection:'Grief famously disrupts sleep — the mind replaying final conversations, funerals, unanswered questions, long into the night. For someone whose nights used to be structured around work shifts abroad and are now structured around loss instead, rest can feel entirely out of reach. David wrote this psalm while genuinely under threat, not in comfortable safety, and still declared peaceful sleep as possible, rooted not in the absence of danger but in trust in God alone. Permission to actually sleep, to let the exhausted body and mind rest even while grief remains unresolved, is not a small thing — it may be one of the most practical mercies you need to receive this season.',
